This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with detecting eye blinking in videos. It could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it involves generating and analyzing videos. Additionally, it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it uses deep generative networks to generate fake videos. Finally, it could also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it aims to expose fake videos generated with neural networks.
